The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the 68th annual National Prayer Breakfast. Pence expresses gratitude for the opportunity to be at the event and thanks Congressman Robert Aderholt for his dedication to public service. He discusses the importance of prayer and faith in American history, citing examples from the founding of the nation to the present day. Pence emphasizes President Trump's belief in prayer and his commitment to religious freedom. He also highlights the administration's efforts to support religious minorities and secure the release of Americans facing persecution for their faith. Pence concludes by thanking the audience for their prayers and encouraging them to continue praying for America.